---
title: "Examining the unique contribution of parent anxiety sensitivity on adolescent neural responses during an emotion regulation task"
collection: publications
category: manuscripts
excerpt: 'This study finds that parent anxiety sensitivity is associated with their adolescent's brain activation in key emotion-regulation regions (like the OFC and ACC) during an fMRI task, with different patterns emerging when adolescents were asked to react versus regulate their emotions.'
date: 2025-04-10
venue: 'Dev Psychopathol'
paperurl: 'https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/40205839/'
citation: 'Church LD, Bounoua N, Stumps A, Matyi MA, Spielberg JM. (2025). &quot;Examining the unique contribution of parent anxiety sensitivity on adolescent neural responses during an emotion regulation task.&quot; <i>Dev Psychopathol</i>. 1-11.'
---
